{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"80325202-1a51-4c6f-8e34-8cf63c06950e","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your crash dump. The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so let me give you the key approaches directly.\n\n## Analyzing a .NET Crash Dump\n\n**Option 1: `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform, recommended)\n```bash\n# Install the tool\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Open the dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n\n# Useful commands inside the analyzer:\n> clrstack          # managed call stack\n> pe                # print last exception\n> dumpheap -stat    # heap overview\n> eestack           # all thread stacks\n```\n\n**Option 2: `lldb` with SOS (Linux/macOS)**\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\n(lldb) clrstack\n(lldb) pe\n```\n\n**Option 3: WinDbg/Visual Studio (Windows)**\nOpen the `.dmp` in Visual Studio or WinDbg with the SOS debugging extension loaded.\n\n---\n\n**Quick triage steps:**\n1. Run `pe` (print exception) to see if an unhandled exception caused the crash.\n2. Run `clrstack` to see what code was executing.\n3. Run `clrthreads` then `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` to inspect other threads.\n\nWould you like help running any of these commands on your dump file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"16f263d9-6b9a-4497-9a99-e289e9bec2d1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\". So I should not invoke that skill.\n\nI'll help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":459,"requestId":"418E:36C261:64F4C00:6E34CEC:69F164C1"},"id":"3f10450a-4840-40e2-beca-5580c54f46b3","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:54:22.434Z","parentId":"21